http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/telangana/Students-observe-bandh/article14023926.ece

In the wake of a nation-wide university bandh call given by the students’ Joint Action Committee of the University of Hyderabad (UoH) over a Dalit scholar’s suicide, the students of Satavahana University in Karimnagar town observed the bandh on Wednesday.Activists belonging to the Students Federation of India (SFI) and others staged a dharna in front of the University main gate and also set fire to an effigy of the Union government demanding justice to the Dalit scholar’s family.Similarly, the Bahujana Students Forum (BSF) also staged a dharna at Telangana chowk in Karimnagar town by raising slogans against the Central government.